    "title": "Six new dnsmasq vulnerabilities open the door to DNS cache poisoning, local root",
    "description": "Recent disclosures have revealed that open-source networking tool dnsmasq is grappling with a serious set of vulnerabilities. The problems span memory safety and input validation, with researchers identifying heap buffer overflows, heap corruption, and code execution bugs among the issues. Taken together, the security flaws open the door to various attacks: poisoning cached DNS entries, slipping past security controls, crashing the dnsmasq process, and in certain scenarios, escalating privileges",
    "source_url": "https://www.helpnetsecurity.com/2026/05/12/dnsmasq-vulnerabilities-cve/",
